# Prisma And Blog Domain

- There is no `Blog` model in Prisma; blog content is represented by `Article`.
- `Article` domain fields to preserve: `title`, `slug`, `content`, `excerpt`, `coverImg`, `status`, `readTime`, `tags`, `publishedAt`, `categoryId`, `userId`.
- `ArticleStatus` enum is authoritative: `DRAFT`, `PUBLISHED`, `ARCHIVED`.
- Existing blog listing behavior queries only `PUBLISHED` articles ordered by `publishedAt` descending and includes `category`.
- Keep slug generation consistent with existing utility patterns (`generateSlug`) when creating article records.
- Preserve model relations and ownership rules:
  - `Article -> User` (required)
  - `Article -> Category` (optional)
  - `Article -> Comment[]`
- For admin article update flow, preserve publish-transition behavior (draft to published controls `publishedAt` assignment).
- When editing Prisma schema/migrations, avoid unrelated changes to other models/enums.
